The paper introduces a method for explaining predictions of Bayesian predictive models using a combination of Local Interpretable Model-agnostic Explanations (LIME) and Bayesian projection predictive variable selection methods. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), statistics (cs.ST), and information theory (cs.IT).
